#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:1
msgid "Launching Kernels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:3
msgid ""
"Writing a kernel is only half the story. The host must load device code, "
"configure the launch grid, marshal arguments, and dispatch the work to the "
"GPU. The primary cuda-oxide launch path is `#[cuda_module]`: it embeds the "
"generated device artifact into the host binary and generates typed launch "
"methods. The lower-level `load_kernel_module` and `cuda_launch!` APIs remain "
"available when you need explicit sidecar loading or custom launch code; note "
"`cuda_launch!` is unsafe and must be wrapped in `unsafe { }`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:12
msgid ""
"[CUDA Programming Guide -- Execution Configuration](https://docs.nvidia.com/"
"cuda/cuda-programming-guide/#execution-configuration) for the authoritative "
"reference on `<<<grid, block, smem, stream>>>` semantics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:16
msgid "The launch lifecycle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:18
msgid "Every kernel launch follows the same sequence:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:20
msgid "**Initialize a CUDA context** -- bind to a GPU device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:21
msgid ""
"**Load the device module** -- usually from the embedded artifact bundle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:22
msgid "**Look up the kernel function** -- by its PTX entry point name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:23
msgid ""
"**Configure the grid** -- block dimensions, grid dimensions, shared memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:24
msgid "**Launch** -- enqueue the kernel on a stream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:25
msgid "**Synchronize** -- wait for results (explicit or implicit)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:31
msgid ""
"The kernel launch lifecycle. The host initializes a context, loads the "
"device module, configures the grid, and launches via a typed method. The GPU "
"scheduler dispatches blocks to SMs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:36
msgid ""
"In practice, `#[cuda_module]` handles steps 2--5 behind a generated Rust "
"API. You normally interact with context creation, `kernels::load`, and a "
"typed method call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:40
msgid "`#[cuda_module]` -- typed arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:42
msgid ""
"Wrap kernels in an inline `#[cuda_module]` module to generate a typed loader "
"and one method per `#[kernel]`. The generated signature checks kernel "
"arguments, but a raw `LaunchConfig` does not prove the kernel's indexing "
"shape or resource requirements. The raw launch method is therefore unsafe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:47
msgid ""
"raw LaunchConfig   -> unsafe launch\n"
"PreparedLaunch<K>  -> safe launch of exactly K\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:52
msgid ""
"\"Synchronous\" here means that you provide a stream and enqueue "
"immediately; GPU execution can still overlap the host until you synchronize."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:55
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{cuda_module, kernel, thread, DisjointSlice};\n"
"use cuda_core::{CudaContext, DeviceBuffer, LaunchConfig};\n"
"\n"
"#[cuda_module]\n"
"mod kernels {\n"
"    use super::*;\n"
"\n"
"    #[kernel]\n"
"    pub fn vecadd(a: &[f32], b: &[f32], mut c: DisjointSlice<f32>) {\n"
"        let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"        let i = idx.get();\n"
"        if let Some(c_elem) = c.get_mut(idx) {\n"
"            *c_elem = a[i] + b[i];\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"fn main() {\n"
"    let ctx = CudaContext::new(0).unwrap();\n"
"    let stream = ctx.default_stream();\n"
"    let module = kernels::load(&ctx).unwrap();\n"
"\n"
"    let a = DeviceBuffer::from_host(&stream, &[1.0f32; 1024]).unwrap();\n"
"    let b = DeviceBuffer::from_host(&stream, &[2.0f32; 1024]).unwrap();\n"
"    let mut c = DeviceBuffer::<f32>::zeroed(&stream, 1024).unwrap();\n"
"\n"
"    // SAFETY: this is a 1D launch and all three buffers contain 1024 "
"elements.\n"
"    unsafe {\n"
"        module.vecadd(&stream, LaunchConfig::for_num_elems(1024), &a, &b, "
"&mut c)\n"
"    }\n"
"    .expect(\"Kernel launch failed\");\n"
"\n"
"    let result = c.to_host_vec(&stream).unwrap();\n"
"    assert_eq!(result[0], 3.0);\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

