#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:277
msgid "Typed async launch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:279
msgid ""
"With the `cuda-host` async feature enabled, `#[cuda_module]` also generates "
"borrowed and owned async methods. These return lazy `DeviceOperation` values "
"instead of enqueuing immediately. No stream is specified at launch time -- "
"the scheduling policy chooses one when the operation is executed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:284
msgid ""
"use cuda_async::device_context::init_device_contexts;\n"
"use cuda_async::device_operation::DeviceOperation;\n"
"\n"
"init_device_contexts(0, 1)?;\n"
"let module = kernels::load_async(0)?;\n"
"\n"
"// SAFETY: this is 1D, buffers contain 1024 elements, and module/scheduler "
"share a context.\n"
"let op = unsafe {\n"
"    module.vecadd_async(\n"
"        LaunchConfig::for_num_elems(1024),\n"
"        &a_dev,\n"
"        &b_dev,\n"
"        &mut c_dev,\n"
"    )\n"
"}?;\n"
"\n"
"// Execute and wait\n"
"op.sync()?;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:305
msgid ""
"Use the owned form when the operation must be spawned or stored as a "
"`'static` future:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:308
msgid ""
"use std::future::IntoFuture;\n"
"\n"
"// SAFETY: this is 1D, owned buffers contain 1024 elements, and contexts "
"match.\n"
"let op = unsafe {\n"
"    module.vecadd_async_owned(\n"
"        LaunchConfig::for_num_elems(1024),\n"
"        a_dev,\n"
"        b_dev,\n"
"        c_dev,\n"
"    )\n"
"}?;\n"
"\n"
"let (a_dev, b_dev, c_dev) = tokio::spawn(op.into_future()).await??;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:324
msgid "Async buffer lifetimes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:326
msgid "Async launches are lazy, so pointer lifetimes matter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:328
msgid ""
"raw pointer shape:\n"
"  build op from CUdeviceptr\n"
"  drop buffer\n"
"  run op later  -> stale pointer\n"
"\n"
"borrowed typed shape:\n"
"  build op from &DeviceBuffer\n"
"  Rust keeps the buffer borrowed until op completes\n"
"\n"
"owned typed shape:\n"
"  move DeviceBox into op\n"
"  spawned task owns the allocation until completion\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:343
msgid ""
"For a contracted kernel, both async forms accept `&PreparedLaunch<K>` and "
"are safe. `cuda_launch_async!` remains a lower-level unsafe migration API; "
"its invocation must be inside an `unsafe` block. Raw pointer async launches "
"are only correct when the caller can prove that the allocation outlives the "
"lazy operation."
msgstr ""

