#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:356
msgid "Composing GPU work"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:358
msgid ""
"`DeviceOperation` supports functional composition. Chain operations with "
"`and_then` and run independent work in parallel with `zip!`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:361
msgid ""
"use cuda_async::zip;\n"
"\n"
"let forward_pass = layer1_op\n"
"    .and_then(|output1| layer2_op(output1))\n"
"    .and_then(|output2| layer3_op(output2));\n"
"\n"
"// Run two independent operations concurrently\n"
"let combined = zip!(branch_a, branch_b);\n"
"let (result_a, result_b) = combined.sync()?;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:373
msgid ""
"Each operation in the chain is scheduled onto a stream only when it "
"executes. The `and_then` combinator passes the output of one operation as "
"input to the next, forming a lazy computation graph."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:378
msgid ""
"The [Async GPU Programming](../async-programming/the-device-operation-model."
"md) section covers `DeviceOperation`, scheduling policies, and stream "
"management in depth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:383
msgid "Cluster launch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:385
msgid ""
"Thread Block Clusters (Hopper and newer) allow blocks to cooperate beyond "
"shared memory via **distributed shared memory** (DSMEM). To launch with "
"clusters, add `#[cluster_launch]` to the kernel and include `cluster_dim` in "
"the launch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:389
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{kernel, cluster, cluster_launch, DisjointSlice};\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"#[cluster_launch(4, 1, 1)]\n"
"pub fn cluster_kernel(mut out: DisjointSlice<u32>) {\n"
"    let rank = cluster::block_rank();\n"
"    // Blocks 0-3 can communicate via DSMEM\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:400
msgid ""
"On the host, the launch uses `launch_kernel_ex` (the extended launch API) "
"with cluster dimensions. `cuda_launch!` supports this via the `cluster_dim` "
"field:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:403
msgid ""
"// SAFETY: args/config match cluster_kernel, including its 4-block cluster;\n"
"// out_dev stays live through synchronization.\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    cuda_launch! {\n"
"        kernel: cluster_kernel,\n"
"        stream: stream,\n"
"        module: module,\n"
"        config: config,\n"
"        cluster_dim: (4, 1, 1),\n"
"        args: [slice_mut(out_dev)]\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
".expect(\"Cluster launch failed\");\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:420
msgid ""
"Cluster launch requires **Hopper (sm_90)** or newer. The maximum cluster "
"size is typically 16 blocks. Use `cargo oxide build --arch sm_90` to target "
"Hopper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:424
msgid "Cooperative launch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:426
msgid ""
"Grid-wide barriers (`cuda_device::grid::sync()` or `this_grid().sync()`) "
"only work when every block in the grid is resident on the device at the same "
"time. A **cooperative launch** asks the driver to guarantee exactly that; "
"without it, blocks that have not been scheduled yet can never reach the "
"barrier and the kernel deadlocks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:432
msgid ""
"On the typed `#[cuda_module]` path, mark the kernel with "
"`#[cooperative_launch]`. Every generated launch method (sync, async, and "
"owned-async) then submits through `cuLaunchKernelEx` with the "
"`CU_LAUNCH_ATTRIBUTE_COOPERATIVE` attribute set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:437
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{cooperative_launch, grid, kernel, DisjointSlice};\n"
"\n"
"#[cuda_module]\n"
"mod kernels {\n"
"    use super::*;\n"
"\n"
"    #[kernel]\n"
"    #[cooperative_launch]\n"
"    pub fn grid_sync_kernel(mut out: DisjointSlice<u32>) {\n"
"        // ... per-block work ...\n"
"        grid::sync();\n"
"        // ... grid-wide post-barrier work ...\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"let module = kernels::load(&ctx)?;\n"
"// SAFETY: config satisfies the kernel's indexing, residency, and output "
"bounds.\n"
"unsafe { module.grid_sync_kernel(&stream, config, &mut out_dev) }?;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:458
msgid ""
"Unlike `#[cluster_launch]`, the attribute changes nothing in the PTX; it "
"only changes how the host submits the launch. The two attributes may be "
"combined on one kernel, in which case both launch attributes go into the "
"same `cuLaunchKernelEx` call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:463
msgid ""
"The legacy (caller-unsafe) `cuda_launch!` macro offers the same behaviour "
"through its `cooperative: true` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/launching-kernels.md:467
msgid ""
"The whole grid must fit on the device in a single wave, or the driver "
"rejects the launch with `CUDA_ERROR_COOPERATIVE_LAUNCH_TOO_LARGE`. Size the "
"grid from `cuOccupancyMaxActiveBlocksPerMultiprocessor` (blocks per SM × SM "
"count) when in doubt."
msgstr ""

